[China has officially reported, so far, ASF in 2 provinces: Henan and Liaoning (see OIE's ASF map at https://tinyurl.com/y899xbvf; click on northeast China, then zoom in). However, epidemiological investigation indicated that the pigs found infected in Henan had traveled thousands of kilometers from a farm in Jiamusi city in China's northeastern province of Heilongjiang, bordering Russia. It is thus highly probable that the additional infected province, Jiangsu, is in fact China's 4th infected province (see 20180817.5969883).

Map of China: http://www.lib.utexas.edu/maps/middle_east_and_asia/txu-pclmaps-oclc-747676570-china_admin-2011.jpg.
HealthMap/ProMED-mail map: Lianyungang, Jiangsu Province, China: https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=5975008,29017

ProMED-mail subscriber David Thomson comments: "[There is] a lot of potential for [ASF] spread in China, and we have just begun to see a small piece of the iceberg. To further assess the potential implications of this, perhaps a reasonable place to look might be the international natural hog casings trade, in particular, origin substitution within that trade." - Mod.AS]
